title: Westlife - Coast To Coast
description:
Coast to Coast was the second studio album by Irish boy-band Westlife. It was released on 6 November 2000, peaking at #1 in the UK and #40 in Australia.

The album produced many hit singles, namly "Against All Odds", "My Love", "What Makes a Man", and "Uptown Girl".

"I Lay My Love on You" and "When You&#039;re Looking Like That" were also released as singles in selected European and Asian territories. The band also recoreded spanish versions of the two songs and were included on the Latin America/Spanish album version.

The album remains as the 4th biggest selling album in Southeast Asia, moving 1.4 Million copies, tailing behind Michael Learns To Rock, Whitney Houston, and Celine Dion.

A deluxe asian edition of the album was later released along with a bonus disc.
